        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-04-12T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-04-12T05:00:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <head>277. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Consulate General at
                        Jerusalem</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d277fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 674.84A/4–1256. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                        >Niact</gloss>. Received at 8:08 a.m. Repeated <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                            >niact</gloss> to Cairo and priority to Amman, Beirut, Baghdad,
                        Damascus, London, Paris, and Tel Aviv.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Jerusalem</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-04-12T12:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1956—noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>414. Colonel Hommel of <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss> has given me
                    morning April 12 following details respecting messages exchanged between <gloss
                        target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> and Israelis in course his talks with
                        <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>.</p>
                <p>In message sent April 11 <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> apprised
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName> that <persName
                        corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName> had accepted proposals regarding
                    cease-fire through observance Article II, paragraph 2 <gloss target="#t_GAA1"
                        >GAA</gloss> in its entirety (ConGentel 404<note n="2" xml:id="d277fn2">
                        <ref target="#d256">Document 256</ref>.</note>).</p>
                <p>A second message was received at <gloss target="#t_UNTSO1">UNTSO</gloss>
                    headquarters from <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> for <persName
                        corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName> somewhat later along following
                    lines. <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> expressed himself as pleased
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGD1">Ben Gurion</persName>’s agreement keep patrols
                    500 meters back from D/<gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> while <persName
                        corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName>-<persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName> talks in progress. Referring again <persName
                        corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>’s acceptance cease-fire <gloss
                        target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> pointed out that since both sides have
                    accepted he urged steps be taken at once implement undertaking.</p>
                <p>However, before arrival second message Hommel had received <persName
                        corresp="#p_SM1">Sharett</persName>’s reply to first message.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d277fn3">See <ref target="#d274">Document 274</ref>.</note> Reply
                    referred renewed outbreaks Fedayeen activities night April 11 and stated inter
                    alia utter falseness <pb facs="0555" n="527" xml:id="pg_527"/>
                    <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1">Nasser</persName>’s assurances stands exposed
                    thereby, etc. (Understand full text already transmitted by Tel Aviv.) Hommel has
                    not therefore delivered <gloss target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> second message
                    to <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss>. He is reporting fully to <gloss
                        target="#t_UNSYG1">UNSYG</gloss> and expects some further communication in
                    response <persName corresp="#p_SM1">Sharett</persName>’s message.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Cole</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
